pageContext.associations: This was found with three others (Nos. 2, 3 & 4, Plate I) in hard gravel, apparently the remains of a [...] or ancient road through a boggy field. The Museum Register states that these were forwarded by Mrs. Tyrell of Ballinderry & that they were found "together with several bones."
